details.description: The only home town coffee company in landis. We love serving good organic coffee. We serve a unique line of pastries and yummy gluten free options as well. Our best sellers are the Willowbrook latte, Vanilla Caramel Latte, and the Coffee United. Use our menu link to order online for an easy pick up on the go or sit and stay with us. Sip from our custom unique in house cups and shop our plant bar selections!!

This is a fantastic coffee shop! I had the Country Maple iced coffee and a maple bacon bagel, and both were excellent. The coffee was flavorful, and the bagel was loaded with bacon. The ladies inside were incredibly nice and professional. Overall, it's a great place to go. Highly recommend!
Amazing coffee and the staff were so sweet!!! Such a beautifully decorated spot. Was just passing through but wish I’d gotten to stay and hang out!
Stopped in here while on a little weekend getaway. Cute spot for sure, nice atmosphere to sit and have coffee and conversation. The staff was also very nice.
Enjoyed stopping at this cute little coffee shop during a recent road trip. The coffee was great and the staff were super friendly and helpful. Definitely would go again!

I love EVERYTHING about this little coffee shop!! It starts with the amazingly sweet and friendly staff who are always helpful and attentive, and is followed by deliciously crafted coffee drinks and pastries. The decor and design of the shop is so cute, warm, and inviting. Added bonus: they sell plants and cute knickknacks made by local artists/vendors, and their branded/logo hats, tees, and sweatshirts are also a must. I highly recommend Willowbrook Grounds if you’re looking for great coffee, service, and atmosphere!

Every time I've been in the place has had a nice relaxed atmosphere. They use coffee from a local roaster in mooresville, and they have a large variety of drinks. They have a variety of pastries too, including gluten -free options for people with allergies like my wife. It's always a nice visit and they have a rotating list of drinks that vary with the season so there's always something new to try. The country maple is subtle but very tasty and my partner loves the cinnamon vanilla. Owners are very friendly and always happy to make recommendations or give you the heads up on sweets and upcoming items.
There teas are good but over all it’s a bit uppity. Didn’t feel very welcoming the few times we have gone in. Coffee is ok but there’s definitely better in the area with a more welcoming atmosphere.

I really hope you come back and try a different menu item on the house and give the girls a chance to meet your needs! We love everyone!

reviews_data.review_text:
Baristas were friendly and welcoming. Almost no wait since they were finishing up a big order when we arrived.
Only reason I can't rate them 5 stars is because the coffee was very weak to me. I ordered a latte and understand that's mostly milk, but I'm used to more than just flavored milk (which is what I got) when I order a latte. No coffee flavor at all. Probably a great spot for anyone who prefers light roast coffees - I prefer medium-dark roasts.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey thanks so much for your review!! So sorry you didn’t think your coffee was strong enough. Typically we are known for having a strong coffee flavor. I’m wondering if you ordered hot because we had some issues with our grinders output last week and we were worried about this affect. Also we have a sweeter menu and a stronger menu, typically we can steer you in the right direction to order if it’s your first time. We aren’t a light roast shop, hoping it’s a one time error. Please come back and try again letting us know your thoughts for a remake of your drink next time!! Thanks!
